then have to let the mortar cure before adding more rocks, to avoid collapse.&nbsp; The rock has all been gathered either from my own property or adjoining land in the forest.&nbsp; I have 20 pickup loads stacked up outside so far.<br />RR<br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/09-30/861889463-Mushroom_house_back_wall_001a.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/09-30/861889463-thumb_Mushroom_house_back_wall_001a.jpg\"></a> <a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/09-30/861889486-Mushroom_house_back_wall_020a.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/09-30/861889486-thumb_Mushroom_house_back_wall_020a.jpg\"></a>"}}